b'' b'' b' if anyone has any information about the existence or location of a' b' dedicated x server kernel for the sun3, please send email. i am' b" trying to put some neglected sun3s to good use but they don't have" b' enough memory for sunos thanks in advance for any help.' b'' b"there is a free program called 'xkernel' which does just that." b'boots a limited kernel which allows you to run x. we converted b'machines over this semester and the speedup is enormously appreciable' b'-- i find them faster than an ncd 15inch black&white xterminal that we' b'are playing with, and a bigger screen to boot! as a matter of fact,' b'the department just bought some old sun3s at an auction to convert!' b'' b'} xkernel is available for anonymous ftp from ftp.ctr.columbia.edu' b'} in /xkernel/xkernel.shar (/xkernel is a symlink to the' b'} latest version of xkernel)' b'' b'note that the compiled version which is available is for the' b'sun but compiling to work for a sun 3/1xx should be quite easy.' b'' b'i am not connected with xkernel except as a satisfied' b'installer and user i may be able to answer questions; feel free' b'to email me.' b'' b'systems programmer and ta, tufts university computer science dept.' b"230- all transfers are disclaimed by my host name and boss's address." b"230- if you don't like this policy, disconnect now!" b'' 